Package fs.fibu2.data.model

Interface Summary
EntrySeparator An EntrySeparator is an entity which separates a set of entries into 'entries which are less than or equal to me' and 'entries which are larger than me'.
 

Class Summary
AbstractAccount This represents the minimal information an fsfibu2 account usually requires: An invoice number which has to exist, if the entry value is negative.
Account This interface represents an fsfibu2 account, i.e.
AccountLoader This class maintains a map of account id's to account objects.
BankAccount This class represents a bank account, i.e.
CashBox This class represents a cash box.
Category Implements a category specification for fsfibu2 entries.
Entry This class represents an fsfibu2 journal entry.
ExtremeSeparator An extreme separator is a separator which comes before all entries or after all entries.
Journal This class implements an fsfibu2 journal.
ReadingPoint A reading point is essentially a day of the year at which the user wants to take a bilancial overview of his journal and perhaps reset all bilancial sums.
